President Donald Trump has issued a proclamation declaring April 23-29, 2017, as National Volunteer Week in the United States. In the proclamation, he celebrates the spirit of compassion and generosity that drives individuals to care for others and recognizes the contributions of America's volunteers. Trump highlights the commitment of citizens to improving the lives of others, both within the country and around the world. He mentions the significant number of Americans who volunteered in 2015 and the high volunteer rates among seniors and busy adults aged 35 to 54. The proclamation pays tribute to various organizations that provide opportunities for volunteers and encourages all Americans to observe the week by participating in service projects and making service a part of their daily lives.